animals. (Left column) Elements A, B, and C are related in ways specific to each type of organization. (Middle column) Hippocampal activation in (a) associative (Zeithamova et al. 2012), (b) sequential (Ezzyat & Davachi 2014), and (c) schematic (Zalesak & Heckers 2009) memory organizations. (Right column) Graphs depicting the results in memory performance of rats with hippocampal lesions compared to a control group without lesions. (a) Rats with hippocampal lesions succeed in learning individual elements and associations (AB and BC) but fail in linking indirectly related elements in an associative organization (reflected in the low preference for the indirectly related element association AC) (Bunsey & Eichenbaum
