Page 27
1996). (b) Rats with hippocampal lesions succeed in remembering items in a list but fail in remembering the order of the items in the sequential organization (Fortin et al. 2002). (c) Rats with hippocampal lesions succeed in learning trained choices of all pairings in a fiveitem hierarchy (A–E; B over C and C over D are shown) but fail in inferring relations between indirectly related elements (B and D) in a hierarchical schematic organization (Dusek & Eichenbaum 1997).

